    "Robert Langer is a scientist and professor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, where he leads the eponymous Langer Lab.",
    "Langer was a founding shareholder of Cambridge, Mass.-based biotech firm Moderna; he owns a 3% stake in the company and has never sold a share.",
    "He also owns shares in SQZ Biotechnologies and Frequency Therapeutics, both of which were founded by postdoc students from his lab.",
    "Langer is estimated to be the most cited engineer in history, with more than 320,000 citations and more than 1,500 articles published.",
    "He also holds more than 1,400 patents, which have been licensed more than 400 times to biotech and pharma companies."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Langer has received more than 200 prizes throughout his career, including the National Medals of Science and Technology.",
    "He has been dubbed the \"Edison of Medicine\" for his work in biomedical engineering."
